f subsection (a), the term “Inspector General” in section 1034 of such title 10 shall mean the Inspector General of the Department of Commerce.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id6c785786-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s3071/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Regulations regarding protected communications and prohibition of retaliatory personnel actions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary may prescribe regulations to carry out the application of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s1034"},"text":"section 1034 of title 10","children":[],"tail":" to the commissioned officer corps of the Administration, including by prescribing such administrative procedures for investigation and appeal within the commissioned officer corps as the Secretary considers appropriate."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id6c785787-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/372/tII/s261"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–372, title II, § 261","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2002-12-19"},"text":"Dec. 19, 2002","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/116/3091"},"text":"116 Stat. 3091","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/259/tII"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–259, title II","children":[],"tail":", §§ 205(a), 207, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2020-12-23"},"text":"Dec. 23, 2020","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/134/1166"},"text":"134 Stat. 1166","children":[],"tail":", 1168; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/263/dK/tCXVII/s11705/c"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–263, div. K, title CXVII, § 11705(c)","